                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1756">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/173.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 4, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Panaman President signed, to-day, contract with Hebard and Company, to construct
                    railway in the province adjoining Costa Rica. Cost estimated at million dollars
                    and a half. Details of bond issue left for consultation with State Department,
                    Washington. It is contemplated encumbering income from six million loan in New
                    York City.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
